//    - Interface thermal resistance
//    - Surface roughness effects
//
// 2. ENHANCED INTERFACES:
//    - Metal-air surface tension (standard)
//    - Substrate-metal interface tension (new)
//    - Contact angle for wetting behavior
//
// 3. LIFT-SPECIFIC PARAMETERS:
//    - Ejection velocity and droplet size scales
//    - Interface transport enhancement
//    - Substrate constraint factors
//    - Nucleation characteristics
//
// 4. TEMPERATURE DEPENDENCE:
//    - Viscosity variation with temperature
//    - Surface tension temperature effects
//    - More realistic material behavior
//
// 5. OPTIMIZED STABILITY:
//    - Reduced interface compression for substrate system
//    - Enhanced transport properties
//    - Better numerical characteristics
//
